“Echo-Skin Composer: A wearable device that translates the electrostatic resonance data from echo-skin mapping into a generative musical score. The intensity and pattern of the ‘echoes’ become the notes, timbre, and rhythm. Users can manipulate the device’s algorithms to shape the music, essentially composing with the *memory* of touch. It’s like listening to the ghosts of hands! I’m going to call it ‘Resonance Bloom’ – it’s got a lovely ring to it, don’t you think?”